==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moabite stone
<hw>Mo"ab*ite stone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Archaeol.)</fld> <def>A
block of black basalt, found at Dibon in Moab by <person>Rev. F. A.
Klein</person>, Aug. 19, 1868, which bears an inscription of thirty-four
lines, dating from the 9th century <sc>b. c.</sc>, and written in the
Moabite alphabet, the oldest Phoenician type of the Semitic alphabet. It
records the victories of <persfn>Mesha</persfn>, king of
<xex>Moab</xex>, esp. those over Israel (<au>2 Kings iii. 4, 5,
27</au>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moabitish</ent>⟦br⟧
